@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title State Machine - psql/DbSystem
skinparam state {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
}
left to right direction
hide empty description
state "Observe" as observe
state "EvaluateReady" as evaluate_ready
state "Ready" as ready
state "Retryable" as retryable
state "Failed" as failed
observe : read spec, tracked status, delete intent,\nand current OCI lifecycle
state "ResolveByLookup" as resolve_by_lookup
state "RejectUnsupportedDrift" as reject_unsupported_drift
state "ApplyUpdate" as apply_update
state "DeletePending" as delete_pending
state "Deleted" as deleted
state "DeleteCleanupBlocked" as delete_cleanup_blocked
[*] --> observe : CreateDbSystem
observe --> resolve_by_lookup : tracked identity missing
resolve_by_lookup --> evaluate_ready : lookup or create reaches\nACTIVE, NEEDS_ATTENTION
resolve_by_lookup --> retryable : OCI state in CREATING,\nUPDATING, DELETING
resolve_by_lookup --> failed : unresolved OCI error or non-success state
observe --> evaluate_ready : OCI state in ACTIVE,\nNEEDS_ATTENTION
observe --> retryable : OCI state in CREATING,\nUPDATING, DELETING
observe --> failed : unresolved OCI error or non-success state
evaluate_ready --> reject_unsupported_drift : force-new or conflicting\ndrift detected
reject_unsupported_drift --> ready : wait for spec or live state change
evaluate_ready --> apply_update : supported mutable drift for\ndbConfigurationParams.applyConfig,\ndbConfigurationParams.configId,\ndefinedTags (+5 more)
apply_update --> ready : update path completes
evaluate_ready --> ready : no supported drift remains
ready --> ready : no supported drift remains
retryable --> retryable : OCI remains retryable
failed --> failed : OCI remains terminal
ready --> delete_pending : delete requested
retryable --> delete_pending : delete requested
failed --> delete_pending : delete requested
delete_pending --> delete_cleanup_blocked : cleanup or finalizer release remains blocked
delete_cleanup_blocked --> deleted : retry delete completion until allowed
deleted --> deleted : terminal stutter
note right of ready
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-controller-state-machine.svg
Start from the shared controller phase model and
specialize imported provider states, delete
targets, and failure exits here.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers map provider states into the shared
controller phases with explicit finalizer and
requeue policies.
service: psql
slug: dbsystem
kind: DbSystem
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required /
retain-until-confirmed-delete
requeue: provisioning, updating, terminating
provider states: create CREATING; update
UPDATING; delete DELETING
supported drift:
dbConfigurationParams.applyConfig,
dbConfigurationParams.configId, definedTags,
description (+4 more)
reject before mutate: force-new fields
compartmentId, dbVersion, instanceCount,
instanceMemorySizeInGBs (+7 more)
create-only fields:
adminPassword.secret.secretName,
adminUsername.secret.secretName, configId,
credentials (+2 more)
list lookup: oci_psql_db_systems filters
compartmentId, displayName; tracked OCI ID via
GetDbSystem wins; otherwise exact compartmentId
plus displayName unique match in ACTIVE,
CREATING, UPDATING, INACTIVE, or
NEEDS_ATTENTION; duplicate matches fail
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
Handwritten DbSystem bind first checks the
tracked OCID with GetDbSystem, then searches
ListDbSystems for an exact compartment plus
displayName match, rereads a single candidate
through GetDbSystem, and fails on ambiguous
duplicates instead of guessing.
Create resolves inline credentials or
same-namespace admin secret refs, stamps only
non-empty secret refs into status, and does not
write follow-up Kubernetes secrets.
Create and update do not poll work requests
directly; provider-backed completion is modeled
through GetDbSystem lifecycle projection with
one-minute requeues while OCI reports CREATING,
UPDATING, or DELETING.
ACTIVE, INACTIVE, and NEEDS_ATTENTION settle as
Active unless the reconcile is already in update
or delete follow-up, and delete retains the
finalizer until GetDbSystem or ListDbSystems
confirms the DbSystem is deleted or not found.
end note
note right of delete_pending
delete policy: required
delete observe: GetDbSystem or ListDbSystems
delete targets: DELETED
end note
@enduml
